rComments: Such a great professor, I was nervous about taking this course since I am nowhere near a science student but she taught the concepts so well and was genuinely one of the kindest professors I've ever met. She really cared if we actually understood the lesson. Tutorials are easy marks and her tests are fair game. Accessible outside class.

Professor Gamble is one of my favourite teachers I have ever had. She's so caring, and she tries so hard to post her lecture material in different formats (i.e. supplemental videos, texts, etc) so the content is accessible for all. Labs are mandatory because they are randomly graded, but the material is engaging and fun. A+

She's a great prof (I've had her in other courses), but she's not used to courses with so many students. She keeps trying to find ways for students to be interactive / actively participate, which is good in theory, but it ends up being frustrating & impractical. Better with upper-year courses with less students.

In both courses Dr. Gamble tried to incorporate different ways of instruction (i.e. lecture, discussion, videos...) which I appreciated. She always had lots of things to say in her feedback -- helpful for the later stuff. Overall she seemed like a caring professor, but with high expectations.

Took ANT208 with her I think reason that the grade average at the end of the course was so high was her attempt to make such a large class more interactive with the class material in tutorials. Was helpful in ensuring that everyone was understanding & staying on top of lectures and applying them in tutorial that way we weren't cramming for exams.
